The Vice President of the United States, Kamala Harris, addressed local leaders in a teleconference, thanking them for their dedication and hard work during the COVID-19 pandemic. She highlighted the progress made in vaccine distribution and the upcoming signing of the American Rescue Plan into law. The plan aims to provide relief to cities, towns, and villages, as well as individuals and businesses. Harris emphasized the importance of equity in distributing relief and announced $250 million in grants for localities to partner with community organizations on health literacy. She encouraged local leaders to continue promoting vaccination, mask-wearing, and other safety measures. Harris acknowledged the challenges faced by local leaders and expressed gratitude for their efforts in serving their communities.